Tim Collins

Tim Collins was a top intercollegiate racer and all American. He raced 470s,
competing at Olympic trials and winning the 470 North American Championship.
He sold the 470s and bought a used 505 with Bill Smith in 1996. They traded up
to a newer 505 in 1997. Tim races with Bill Smith. Tim lives in Rhode Island.
Tim and Bill have been training hard for the World Championship, and recently
won the 505 East Coast Championship, over a star studded field.

